ques.p: To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Olympics, Media and Sport what (a) gifts and (b) corporate entertainment and hospitality (i) he, (ii) other Ministers and (iii) officials from his Department have received on each date since 11 May 2010.

reply.p: Gifts, corporate entertainment and hospitality received by Ministers in the Department since 11 May 2010 are shown in the table:

td.i: Secretary of State for Culture, Olympics, Media and Sport

tr.td: Two tickets to FA Cup Final
7 x DVDs, courtesy of British Film Institute
World Cup England v Algeria. Two tickets provided by FIFA
Two-night stay, High Commissioner's Residence, South Africa
England v Bangladesh Test Match, on invitation from the ICC
World Cup England v USA. Ticket provided by FIFA
Wimbledon Championships, on invitation from All England Lawn Tennis Association
1 x ticket to the FA Cup Final
One-night stay, High Commissioner's Residence, South Africa.

td.i: Minister for Culture, Communications and Creative Industries

tr.td: Dinner, courtesy of the Royal Institute of British Architects.
Ticket to Ivor Novello Awards and Awards Lunch, courtesy of British Academy of Songwriters, Composers and Authors
Ticket to Rambert at Sadler's Wells, courtesy of Sadler's Wells
7 x DVDs, courtesy of British Film Institute
Travel from London to the Founders Forum Symposium, Hampshire
Two-night stay, food and concert tickets at Aldeburgh Festival, courtesy of Britten Pears Foundation
Book, courtesy of the Museum of London
